    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"US Economy 1999 to Present\"\nsubtitle: \"A visual analysis of the current year in the context of every year since 1999\"\n---\n\n\n\nAn interactive drill-down analysis of the US economy placed against every\nyear since 1999. Use the sidebar to move between panels, or click the links\nat the bottom of this page.\n\n::: {.callout-note appearance=\"simple\"}\n**Macro data** comes from FRED (public-domain US government series, refreshed\ndaily). **Market data** (S&P 500, Dow, NASDAQ, VIX, sector returns) is a\ncalibrated synthetic overlay — FRED's proprietary market licenses prohibit\nredistribution of the raw series. The current (partial) year is flagged with\nan asterisk. See [Data & Citations](about.qmd) for the full data dictionary\nand source attribution.\n:::\n\n## 2026 Snapshot {#snapshot}\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div style=\"display:flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; margin: 10px 0 20px;\">\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">Real GDP growth (YoY)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1d3557; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">—</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">No data yet</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">Unemployment rate</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #2f9e44; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">4.3%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">30ᵗʰ percentile (lower = better)</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">CPI inflation (YoY)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #2f9e44; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">2.9%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">65ᵗʰ percentile</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">Fed Funds target</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1d3557; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">3.64%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">Upper bound, period avg</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">10Y Treasury</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1d3557; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">4.22%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">Period avg</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;&#10;       background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);&#10;       min-width: 170px; flex: 1;\">\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.80rem; color:#6c757d; letter-spacing: .02em; text-transform: uppercase;\">S&amp;P 500 (YTD)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: #2f9e44; line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 4px;\">+4.0%</div>\n<div style=\"font-size: 0.82rem; color:#6c757d; margin-top: 2px;\">30ᵗʰ percentile</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Where does the current year sit in the historical range? {#range}\n\nEach bar shows the range of every year since 1999 (excluding the current\npartial year) for a given indicator, with the current year marked.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-fefe5d8ac1aa4abe2bef\" style=\"width:100%;height:325px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-fefe5d8ac1aa4abe2bef\">{\"x\":{\"visdat\":{\"6dac2acb7c1f\":[\"function () \",\"plotlyVisDat\"]},\"cur_data\":\"6dac2acb7c1f\",\"attrs\":{\"6dac2acb7c1f\":{\"alpha_stroke\":1,\"sizes\":[10,100],\"spans\":[1,20],\"x\":{},\"y\":{},\"base\":{},\"type\":\"bar\",\"name\":\"1999–2025 range\",\"marker\":{\"color\":\"rgba(42,111,151,0.28)\",\"line\":{\"color\":\"#2a6f97\",\"width\":1}},\"hovertemplate\":\"%{x}<br>Range: %{base:.2f}% – %{customdata:.2f}%<extra><\\/extra>\",\"customdata\":{},\"width\":0.34999999999999998,\"inherit\":true},\"6dac2acb7c1f.1\":{\"alpha_stroke\":1,\"sizes\":[10,100],\"spans\":[1,20],\"x\":{},\"y\":{},\"type\":\"scatter\",\"mode\":\"markers\",\"name\":\"Median\",\"marker\":{\"symbol\":\"diamond\",\"size\":11,\"color\":\"#1d3557\"},\"hovertemplate\":\"%{x}<br>Median: %{y:.2f}%<extra><\\/extra>\",\"inherit\":true},\"6dac2acb7c1f.2\":{\"alpha_stroke\":1,\"sizes\":[10,100],\"spans\":[1,20],\"x\":{},\"y\":{},\"type\":\"scatter\",\"mode\":\"markers\",\"name\":\"2026*\",\"marker\":{\"symbol\":\"circle\",\"size\":14,\"color\":\"#bc4749\",\"line\":{\"color\":\"#7a1e1f\",\"width\":1}},\"hovertemplate\":\"%{x}<br>2026: %{y:.2f}%<extra><\\/extra>\",\"inherit\":true}},\"layout\":{\"margin\":{\"b\":80,\"l\":50,\"t\":60,\"r\":30},\"title\":{\"text\":\"2026 values vs 1999–2025 range\",\"x\":0.5,\"xanchor\":\"center